animal.description:
Peanut: 4-month-old chocolate and rust male, soon to be neutered, docked tail and natural ears. 12", 8 lbs. Fully vetted. 

Meet Peanut – Peanut is a young, fun, bright little guy.  He is drop dead gorgeous, full of life and he has a spectacular min pin prance.  We are looking for a very special home for this very special boy.

Peanut was dumped in a park when he was 8 weeks old, weighing only 4 pounds.  He was very disoriented and had awful diarrhea.  He was diagnosed with giardia and distemper.  Peanut is a fighter and made it through.  Sadly, though, the distemper left Peanut blind.  Most distemper survivors have residual neurological issues. Peanut gets what we call the “no see ums”.  He will jerk his head back as if something flew close and suddenly at his face.  It is infrequent and seems to be when he wakes up from naps.  Most times we can hold him and comfort him through and they resolve quickly.

In foster care he started feeling better, but the reality of his new existence resulted in a couple weeks of intense fear.  Peanut has learned to trust us and his environment.  He knows several verbal cues and is a quick and eager student.  He enjoys being cuddled and loves his “scritches” and “pets”.  He has begun to trust enough for belly “rubs” especially if they are given in a sunny spot.  We are keeping a list of his verbal cues as this helps him know what to expect when we are handling, feeding and doing activities.   

Peanut is getting used to a harness and leash.  We have been getting him out in a baby sling to get used to different sounds and smells.  He loves these walks and spends part of his outing cuddled and asleep.  He rides well in the car but sometimes gets car sick on longer rides.  This is improving as he gets more exposure.  He loves being outside on sunny days, listening to the sounds of the neighborhood, sniffing the breezes, and soaking up the sun.  He prances around our small patch of lawn executing little goat leaps of joy.  Peanut has some favorite toys he likes to pounce on and shake, he also will play a gentle game of tug.  He will nestle into his snuggle sack and fall asleep in our arms.

He sleeps quietly and happily in an “x” pen overnight.  We also have a play pen if we need him to nap during the day or just a secure place for him. He has his toys and chewie to keep him occupied.

Until Peanut can execute stairs, which we are working on, he has not yet been completely potty trained.  We take him out when he first wakes up and regularly during the day.  He is very good about wearing a belly band and about standing still for “pants” when we need to change his “pants”.  Peanut has been fine around other small dogs and does not seem to have much reaction to them.  He has not been around large dogs or a multi-dog environment.

No apartments for Peanut, he needs to have a yard for serious goat leaps and sunning. No young children as he is still learning that mouth play is not ok.  Also, if he gets fearful, he gets nippy.  He is easy for an adult to handle and control him, but it might be scary and unsafe for a child. 
 
Peanut is an adorable loving little min pin, and will need an experienced home with lots of loving patience while he acclimates to a new household. Blind dogs compensate for their loss of sight with heightened sense of touch, smell, and hearing. He can live a full perfectly normal life with someone that is ready to commit to teaching him how to navigate in a sightless world.  His forever home will need to continue with his established verbal cues while adding new ones.  

Are you the perfect home for dear Peanut? He will be available around the second week of February, after his neuter appointment, so get your application in and approved now!  If you think you have what it takes to be Peanut's forever home, please submit an application today!

Note: Peanut is located in San Mateo County, CA - and we will not fly this boy.

If you wish to adopt, please fill out our IMPS Min Pin Adoption Application at: 
https://minpinrescue.org/home.html

If you have previously submitted an application, there is no need to re-apply.

For more details, contact Sue at:  kellruss@earthlink.net

IMPS is a non-profit rescue organization that does not have a viewing facility to which you can come and meet the dogs available for adoption. All of our dogs are in loving homes in foster care. Arrangements can be made with the foster parent; however, it is a requirement that the Adoption Application be completed and approved first.

If you wish to adopt, please fill out the IMPS MinPin Adoption Application go to:  http://www.minpinrescue.org/home.html 

Please visit our website by going to: http://www.minpinrescue.org

animal.description:
Nina is a LARGE, friendly, goofy dog. Unfornately Nina does not always get along with other dogs or small animals and her previous owners didn't feel they could manage this aggression.
Typical of the Maremma breed, she can be independent and free-thinking. She will require a guardian who can keep her safe but busy so she doesn't get bored, wander, and get herself into trouble. She has a history of jumping fences (under 5ft) Being a guardian breed, Maremmas can be suspicious of strangers but are gentle, affectionate, and very loyal to their families. They do best with gentle but firm and consistent training. They respond to encouragement and positive rewards. She is partially housetrained and knows some basic obedience such as "sit" and "come". Her previous guardians describe her as friendly, calm, and protective. She is used to being indoors and outdoors. Nina gets easily excited and needs lots of exercise and outings with guardian. Good obedience and a confident guardian is important. 

Nina is looking for a confident yet patient guardian, preferably one with breed experience. She has lots of love to give her new guardians! A behaviour counselling session with our Adoption Staff is necessary before adopting any animal to ensure success. 

Please note, due to the current COVID-19 pandemic our adoption process has changed. 
Please visit our website https://spca.bc.ca/adoption/how-to-adopt/ 
for more information and to apply for the animal you are interested in. All adoptions are by appointment only once we have received and approved an application.

*Due to the high number of applications we receive for our animals, we will only be contacting potential adopters to further review their application.

Photos by Simon Hergott Primary Color: White Weight: 36.8kg Age: 5yrs 0mths 1wks Animal has been Spayed

animal.description:
Check out this ladies' man - this is Galio!
He is super sweet, inquisitive, smart and playful!  He already knows how to sit and shake !  Galio is truly a ladies' man, he prefers women companionship while men generally make him uncomfortable. When meeting Galio for the first time, he may be timid and a bit reserved but he does warm up pretty quickly.  A good way to make friends is to offer him yummy snacks. Once he gets to know you he LOVES to have his back scratched as well as behind those cute ears! 
Galio is estimated to be 8 months old and he weighs approximately 65 pounds. He likes other dogs and would do well in a home with another dog. To ensure any dog already in the home is a good match with Galio, a meet and greet will be set up a the shelter prior to adoption.  Galio has shown interest in chasing cats, and would do best in a home without cats at this time.  Galio needs some more practice walking on a leash, but he is getting better every day.  He would love to go exploring and zip around a large backyard.  Because of his size and puppy manners we recommend any children in his forever home are 12 years old and up.  
As part of the adoption process, Galio will need to be signed up for puppy obedience classes.  He is a great dog and with a little training and lots of love he will become the best doggy he can be!  
If you would like to meet Galio, please fill out an adoption application at:  https://wishbonepetrescue.org/    Once the application has been approved an appointment will be set up for you to come in and meet Galio

We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21

animal.description: Meet the marvelous Marcen! Marcen is a approximately 4 year old Plott Hound (we believe he is purebred or pretty close to it) and he weighs approximately 65 lbs. Marcen came to us as an owner surrender through ARATT (Animal Rescue Assistance Team TN) with another dog because their owner could not care for him anymore. Marcen is a big love bug and adores people; he loves attention and is very affectionate. He is learning not to jump up on people and is learning the "sit" command. Marcen walks fairly well on leash; he does pull some, but not extensively. He is also a great car rider and prefers to sit in the front seat so he can look out the window! Marcen is an active guy that requires a lot of exercise, but he does have a lazy side once his energy is curbed. He gets along great with other dogs (he is currently being housed with Coffee) and loves playmates! During his photoshoot, Marcen thoroughly enjoyed playing with Coffee, Willow, and Noah! Marcen has not been tested around cats yet, however he is a hound and most hound breeds tend to have some prey drive towards smaller animals. We believe Marcen would do alright with a dog-savvy cat who was not afraid of him, would not run from him, and wouldn't be afraid to set some boundaries. Marcen loves all people and is good with children; he will accidently knock down a smaller child when he gets over excited. If you are looking for an active buddy to go on long walks and adventures with, look no further than Marcen!

animal.description: Found stray at no fault of his own, Kramer was brought to the shelter. Kramer is about one year old and has tons of potential along with a lot of growing up to do! He is fun-loving, playful, and energetic, but he's also a big goofball that can be a handful at times. He will highly benefit from a home that is able and willing to train an oversized puppy, provide structure, and engage in lots of activities and exercise. Kramer walks well on leash and appears to be housebroken, but crate training and continued housebreaking routines are highly advised for this young fella. He appears to love other dogs, but a formal meet has not been done yet. Dogs will be required to have a supervised visit with staff prior to adoption. We think Kramer would do best with a female dog, who will be tolerant of his puppy shenanigans and be able to help him with his manners. Cats are unknown, and if placed with cats we ask for a very slow, well-managed introduction once in the home. We will only place Kramer with children 14 years or older due to his periodic short spurts of "rough puppy-play. If Kramer is the young, fun, active, and on-the-go guy you've been searching for, please apply to meet him!

Waylon is an adorable 5 month old Heeler mix from a shelter in Kansas. He's a typical pup... loves to play with toys, has a good amount of energy, super loving, and fun. He is fully crate trained and is making great progress with potty training. He's went several days without an accident now. Waylon gets along great with other dogs and has done great with the kiddos he's met so far. He will need lots of exercise and we require our pups get enrolled in training classes after adoption. Neutered, fully vetted and vaccinated, microchipped, and ready for his furever family!
To help pay for vet bills and care (transportation, food, toys, etc..) a $300 donation is requested at the time of adoption. All of our adoptions are contingent upon an approved application, home visit, reference check, obedience training agreement, and signing of adoption contract. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, and microchipped before adoption. Our dogs are companion animals that live indoors as part of your family. Please do not apply if your plan is to have them as outside dogs, garage dogs, porch dogs or outside kennel dogs. We do not ship dogs. All of our dogs are in private foster homes. We are not a shelter with hours. A visit can be arranaged after an adoption questionnaire has been filled out and sent in. Please try email first. We are all volunteers that work so we can not easily take or make phone calls.

animal.description:
Candy Girl ACCT-A-83195

Intake Type: Stray - APO Pickup
Sex: Female
Altered: No
Age: ~2Y

Medical Observation:1/25 (Per Vet Staff)- BAR, friendly

Dog Meets: Sandy & Candy Girl https://youtu.be/7u0Y0U88O3w

Sandler & Candy Girl 2nd meethttps://youtu.be/Ze3sWMm8R9w

Sandler & candy Girl Dog Meet https://youtu.be/yaJe1muxS44

Reggie and Candy Girl-- https://youtu.be/KwRDo8fuubU
Behavior Observation:
(1/25) Staff Evaluation -- 
Kennel Presentation - Easy to leash/social. Wagging tail at front of kennel. Tried to back out of leash a few times but was easy to leash afterwards. On return, entered kennel with ease and allowed me to remove leash.
Leash Skills - Pulls Minimally On Leash. Walks well with infrequent pulling. Walked past a colony cat within 6 feet or so, and Candy Girl either did not see the cat or did not react. Also walked past a dog in a run, and Candy showed no reaction. She did pull towards a man walking about 10 feet away with her tail wagging. Mouthed at leash a few times but no actual leash biting.
Handleability - Loose/Allows all handling. Would jump up on handler and give kisses. Solicited lots of attention in run by leaning head against handler's legs. Affectionate and social. Allowed handling all over, including ears and face. Medium energy level; would sniff around the run, return to handler for attention, then continue exploring.
Tag - Engages in play. Likes to play tag, becomes excited while playing but then settles back down as soon as handler stops.
Toys - Accepts a trade. Loves to play tug-of-war with rope toys, and will bring a rope toy over to handler and press it against legs when she wants to play. Chased ball but didn't take possession. Dropped toy and lost interest when handler stopped playing tug-of-war with her.
Color Level Gold. Playful, easily handled, medium energy level and very friendly.
(1/25) Per APO -- Dog is healthy, very sweet behavior.


This animal is currently available from foster care through ACCT Philly's Adoptions Programs. This animal is not onsite. If the foster has not listed a personal email, contact foster@acctphilly.org to be put in touch with the foster. 

We encourage you to visit our shelter during our adoption hours to view our complete selection of available animals. In preparation for your visit, please make sure to visit http://www.acctphilly.org/adopt/ to review our adoption requirements, hours of operation, upcoming events, and more!

animal.description:
This sweet boy, named Corbie, came into our rescue when we thought he had been shot and thrown into the Landfill. We are thankful he wasn’t shot but he was injured, had a tummy full of rocks and had been discarded like trash.

Fast forward a few months?
Corbie is a handsome male chihuahua that is approximately 1-2 years old. He loves to sit on his foster parents lap. He is such a gentle soul and loves to be with his humans. He goes to bed with them each night but does not stay long, as he likes to spend the night in his kennel at the side of their bed. But he loves to wake them up each morning by jumping into their bed to tell them “Good Morning”. 

Corbie is very smart and learned the dog door within just a few minutes. He like to follow his foster mom around when she is working in the house or the yard. He gets along very well with their dogs and he does well around respectful children 8 and older.

Corbie got a stuffed animal for Christmas and he carries it with him everywhere including to his crate to sleep at night. He also gathers everyone else’s Christmas toy and carries them to his crate too. Funny boy!

Corbie is not a barker unless he joins in with the others. He doesn’t seem to have any food aggression. He is quiet, gentle and loving. He would rather sit on their laps rather than on the sofa with the other dogs. All in all Corbie would make one special family very happy!

animal.breeds_label: Dutch Shepherd & Pit Bull Terrier Mix
animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Caught you looking, but its ok because my foster mom says when you're this handsome, people can't help but stare.

My name is Jace Herondale, Jace for short. I am a young, eager to learn 18 month old who loves to play.

I was adopted as a pup and returned without a lot of skills, but luckily my foster mom is a pro!

Since coming back to Rescue Rovers I have learned the kennel is an ok place to be, how to lay down and be calm in the house, AND how to sit, wait and lay down on command. Foster mom says I am a quick study and need a new family who will keep teaching me new things.

I love to play with other dogs, however, I am so excited most other dogs don't know how to take me and I haven't mastered calming down with new doggy friends yet. A doggy sibling would be great - as long as my people know how to manage those interactions and will keep up on my training.

Now for the important stuff foster mom says I have to tell you...

I am kennel trained now, but I will bark a little when I first go in or if I see someone in the house, because I want out with you.

I am potty trained. I walk well on leash...but do get super excited seeing other people, so she says its a work in process.

I am far too interested in cats to live with one and that goes for smaller dogs as well. For now I would probably do best in a home with no other animals. Also need a home with a fenced back yard because I love chilling there taking in the sun. She says an active home is a must, and if there are kids they need to be older because I love to play.

When I and my siblings first came to Rescue Rovers as little puppies we were listed as pittie mixes. Now as I have grown up, Mom says I look and act much more dutch shepherd mix and she doesn't see any pittie looks or traits in me either...but who knows, right? That's the fun of a rescue!

Anyway, no matter what I am, I'm a handsome boy with tons of potential. If you would like to meet please apply at www.rescuerovers.org

He LOVES to play, receive attention, and keep busy any way he can.  He would make a great hiking, running, or playing partner.  Exercise is the key to a calm, content dog.  Cosmo was adopted as a young puppy but was unfortunately returned when they didn't have enough time for him.  He was stuck in a crate for over 10 hours a day.  We have noticed some protective behaviors that will need to be addressed in his new home.  Cosmo was in foster care a few months ago but returned shortly for this reason.  It seems he is very loyal and can become protective when someone enters a room where he is up on the bed with his person or is standing very close to them.  It will be important for his new family to discourage any guarding behavior and to reassure him that there is no need to protect.  Cosmo bonds closely to his people and will need an experienced owner who can work with a trainer to set these boundaries and ensure success.  Cosmo would thrive in an adult-only (preferably single person) home with limited visitors.

animal.description:
Wow! Check out this handsome boy! Meet Broly! <3 

"Broly is the laziest, sweetest cuddle bug ever! He absolutely loves attention, pets, people and cuddles! He spends 95% of this time sleeping on the couch and the other 5% asking for rubs. He’s very food motivated and will eat his food extremely fast so he would benefit from a slow feeder. Broly is the definition of a big cuddly bear and would do great in almost any home! He’s been the absolute perfect house guest! He’s shown zero signs of aggression and would be happy in a home that can give him a lot of attention and food!"

Ever feel like some dogs were meant to be with you? We sure do! Broly and his friend Ellie recently came into our rescue after they ended up in the shelter. Little did we know when we tagged them that they were actually the two dogs that their owners were hoping to surrender to us a little over a month ago. Sadly, we were full at the time, but we still had them on our foster list. Turns out they were staying with a friend and they escaped and found themselves in the shelter. We don't know what happened during the time they were on their own, but they were in pretty rough shape. We wish we could have taken them in sooner so they could have avoided whatever happened. At least, they are with us now, and won't ever have to worry about being on their own again! 

Broly is a 5 year old male Great Pyrenees. He currently weighs about 83lbs but is on the thin side. Broly is a dog that turns heads. Everyone who sees him wants to meet him. Everyone who meets him falls in love! Broly has such an amazing personality, and he just loves meeting new people! This boy is the perfect candidate to take out and about with you. He has such a winning personality! His personality can be described as calm and laid back. He is pretty lazy but always up for cuddles! His house manners are superb. He can be trusted with free-roam of the house. He has not shown to be a big chewer or barker in his foster home. 

Broly is uninterested in fetch and toys currently. We are unsure if he is a water dog or not. Broly has not shown to have any signs of food aggression or resource guarding in his foster home. He has not shown to be a big hugger and doesn't jump on people. Broly does good on car rides. He is okay on a leash but could use some more working with. We are unsure how he would do in an apartment setting. At night, he likes sleeping in his fosters bed or on a doggie bed. Broly is potty and kennel trained. 

Broly is just about as PYRfect as you can get! I am sure you are already trying to figure out how you can adopt this handsome boy! Before you do, though, here are some things to note about him 

-Broly does good with other dogs. He is initially curious about them and will sniff and give licks. Once he feels comfortable with them, he will even play with them sometimes. 

-Broly has not been around any cats. Given his laid-back personality, we think he would be okay with proper introduction. 

-Broly has been around kids as young as 4 and has done well. 

-Broly is being fostered in Moore, OK. We ask that his new family be able to pick him up, even if they are out of state. 

-Broly would be fine in a home with or without other dogs. His owner should be home most of the day, if they have no other dogs, though. 

So, on a scale of 1-10 (10 being the highest) what is the probability that this guy is coming home with you? Yeah...that is what I thought. Be sure to fill out an adoption app for him at https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app ;) 

His adoption fee is $225. That includes DHLPP, Rabies, and Bordatella shots. He will be micro-chipped, heart-worm tested, have a fecal done, be de-wormed, be spayed/neutered and will be current on heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

Jude is an approximately 2 year old Beagle (mix?) Who was rescued from a shelter in Kentucky when his time was up. Jude is a sweet dog who is probably right at the bubble of 25-30 lbs. His adoption fee is $199 and includes his neuter, microchip, vaccinations and routine labwork. Please email us if interested in adopting Jude.

Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes: 
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*: 
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming 
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old) 
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt: 
If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

animal.description:
Sawyer is a dog on the move! He loves to play and wants a family that will be active with him.

From my foster: "Sawyer knows sit, down and stay. Best of all, he's housebroken!!!!

He loves long walks and kids. He is a bit of a barker when he sees other dogs (he really wants to play with them and just doesn't understand why he can't!). Playing fetch with the tennis ball is one of his ultimate favorite activities. Sawyer will drop the ball for you, or let you take it out of his mouth, he's very gentle that way. Hand feeding him treats isn't a problem at all. He also likes tug-of-war, I have some West Paw Design toys he's grown very fond of. The first few nights he was in the crate he barked a for about an hour. I learned with a long walk, a lot of puppy play time, and some peanut butter in a Kong, he goes to bed more peacefully and will sleep through the night.

He is a ham!!! Since he is a puppy, and puppies have energy, he has his ways of letting you know that he has extra energy. The main way is by stealing one of your shoes and then playing tag. He's a little mischievous there, but he means well. Once you toss a toy in his direction he will willingly give up his prize. When he gets super antsy he can be a little mouthy (not biting, but more of the herding instinct) so he would do really well in a family with kids that will get him running around using up energy. This is not a dog that would do well home alone all day every day. He needs activity. After about 10 minutes of active play time he will happily take a 2 hour nap. By the way, he snores and runs in his sleep- it's adorable."

You are welcome to come to our rescue center during open hours to see all of our great adoptable animals. Thank you for your interest in our animals!

NOTE: Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable, so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

****PROTOCOLE COVID-19****

NOTRE REFUGE RESTE FERMÉ AU PUBLIC. LES ADOPTIONS SERONT GÉRÉES SUR RENDEZ-VOUS UNIQUEMENT LES SAMEDIS.  MERCI 

Mâle Doberman âgé d’environ 5 ans. Vient d’un refuge au Manitoba et servait à la reproduction. Chien n’ayant pas eu beaucoup de stimulations car laissé à lui-même. Vocal, propre, indépendant, forte personnalité, aime beaucoup jouer, grande énergie. Maison et cour clôturée.
Vinnie n’apprécie pas les vétérinaires donc un travail de désensibilisation est à prévoir en ce sens. Aura besoin de gens avec une très grande expérience des chiens et avec du temps pour s’en occuper et le stimuler physiquement et mentalement. L’aide d’un comportementaliste canin serait utile. 
Vinnie est allergique au poulet. Pas d’autres animaux ni enfants ou ados.

Dans l’espace prévu pour les commentaires, veuillez s’il vous plaît nous indiquer votre profil d’adoptant, à savoir tous les renseignements pertinents à votre sujet afin de constater si le chien pourrait être un bon match pour vous. Ainsi, votre expérience avec les chiens, si vous vivez en appartement ou maison, si votre cour est clôturée, les membres de votre famille, si vous avez d’autres animaux...Indiquez bien votre numéro de téléphone. 

SVP ne pas appeler le refuge pour les informations concernant nos animaux en adoption. Merci

Seules les demandes d’adoption retenues recevront un retour de courriel ou un appel téléphonique. 

Frais d’adoption: 340$, incluant la stérilisation, la vaccination et les vermifuges. Il n’y a pas de taxes. 

NOTE: il n’y a pas d’adoption avec enfants de 10 ans et moins



**** COVID-19 PROTOCOL****

OUR SHELTER REMAINS CLOSED TO THE PUBLIC.  ADOPTIONS WILL BE MANAGED BY APPOINTMENT ONLY ON SATURDAYS. THANK YOU !

Male Doberman about 5 years old.  Comes from a shelter in Manitoba and was used for breeding. Dog who has not have much stimulation because left to himself. Vocal, house trained, independant, strong personality, likes very much to play, great energy. House and fenced yard.
Vinnie does not like veterinians so should therefore be gradually desensitized to that. Will need people with a great deal of experience with dogs and with time to take care and stimulate him, physically and mentally. The help of a canine behaviorist is recommanded.
Allergic to chicken
No other animals nor children nor teens.

In the Comments box, please tell us about yourself and why you believe that this dog is a good match for you.  Please include your phone number, your dog experience, whether you live in an apartment or house, members of the household including pets, and whether you have a fenced in yard.  

Please do not call the shelter for information concerning our adoptable animals. Thank you!

Only successful adoption requests will receive a return email or a phone call.

Adoption Fee:  $ 340, including sterilization, vaccination and dewormer.   There are no taxes.

NOTE:  We do not adopt dogs to families with children 10 years of age and under.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Grandma Shark! My previous owner found himself unable to care for me, so I've been patiently waiting for a new home since December 17th. When I first arrived at MACC, I was really nervous. There were so many new people, sounds and smells. I felt safest in my kennel and would bark at people when they got too close. After a few days, I realized that the workers here are really nice and I became more comfortable with them. I really liked all the treats they gave me, playing outside with them and getting pet. I DID NOT like seeing the doctor and getting an exam. I didn't want to be restrained, so I jumped around, wiggled, thrashed and tried to bite. I'm not proud of that part, but what can I say? I don't like to be held or hugged! Besides that, I've been having a great time here! I get to go on walks with the volunteers - who all love me, by the way. I even got to play with another dog in playgroup. I like to be vocal and play rough and rowdy with other dogs. I did get a little too excited while playing and the other dog and I got into a bit of a scuffle. We're both ok though. If I lived with another dog, it would be best if it was a social, tolerant male dog. And of course, a slow introduction would still be best. I think it would be fun to have some young humans to play with too, but maybe not the really young ones. They need to be old enough to understand that I don't like to be hugged. So anyway, if it sounds like I might be the dog for you, call my friends at MACC and ask to meet me, I'll be here waiting!
animal.name: GRANDMA SHARK

,Due to COVID-19, all adoptions will be by appointment only. To adopt, complete our online adoption application and an Adoption Counselor will contact you within 48-hours to schedule your adoption appointment. Momma is a sweet friendly girl who is looking for a loving family she can call her own.  She is scent oriented and likes to follow her nose exploring.  She likes meeting new people and loves attention.  Now all she needs is a chance to show you what a great addition she would be to your family.

To inquire about an adoptable animal from the Louisiana SPCA, please call 504.368.5191, ext. 150 to speak with an adoption counselor.
To see more adoptable animals from the Louisiana SPCA, please go to http://la-spca.org/adopt.



The petfinder.com system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

animal.description:
If the listing is up she is still available, don't write to ask if she is...

Chula is about 2 years old and the sweetest girl, she loves to play fetch and run around the yard at full speed. She likes to be touching you in bed at night and sit on your lap to watch a little t.v. She tolerates the dogs and cats here and likes to pay tug with the puppies.. She is such a happy playful little girl. Her breed is just a guess but she seems to be the best of both of those breeds. Her adoption fee is $350 and she has been spayed, fully vetted and microchipped.

  Please read all info below before proceeding. Please make sure you are ready to adopt before filling out an application. While we don't charge a fee to submit an application we can understand why some rescues do. A lot of time is spent reviewing applications. Time that can be spent caring for the dogs. To do all that only to be told that you now aren't ready or have changed your mind is exhausting. Please read all info posted about the dogs and if we say the dogs needs a fenced yard and you don't have one please don't proceed. We also don't adopt out to home with INVISIBLE/SHOCK FENCING and can provide you some info if you would like to understand why we feel this way. Because these are rescued dogs we don't usually know who the parents are so breed listings are usually an educated guess. PLEASE MAKE SURE YOU ARE WILLING TO MAKE A LIFETIME COMMITMENT TO THIS PET. If you are interested in this dog please go to our website  www.susieqdogresq.com. to fill out an application. A vet reference and home visit are required.  Please check our pet list to see more animals up for adoption.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Kaison! I was born here at the Big Dog Ranch Rescue and adopted out as a very young puppy. I was returned to Big Dog Ranch Rescue because they felt that they didn't have the time or space to accommodate such an active puppy. I am a very sweet boy with an extremely high energy level. I absolutely need to find myself a family that has a home with a great big backyard for me to run around in any release all of my energy. I would prefer an active family who wants to take me for long walks/runs and is interested in engaging in active games, like fetch, with me. Sometimes I can be a little bit mouthy when I am excited, but I'm still a puppy (despite my size) and just need some additional training to learn how to act more appropriately in social situations. Sometimes I can be a little bit possessive when food is around and should probably be fed separately from other animals in the home. I have lived in a home with young children and do quite well with them, but sometimes will knock into them simply due to the fact that I'm not totally aware of my size.

animal.description:
Meet Honey!  Looking for a companion that is as sweet as honey?  Well this may be the girl for you! This sweet girl has lost both her home and her owner due to financial issues.  She was placed in a shelter in Rhode Island where the shelter staff loved her very much, but Honey did not do very well in that loud and busy environment.  This girl needed out fast and a big comfy couch to snuggle on.  The shelter in Rhode Island sent out a plea to SNARR and as usual SNARR could not say no. Honey is now in foster where she is just thriving. Her foster mom says she is the easiest and sweetest dog she has ever had. This little girl is just a bundle of love. She may be shy at first, but once she warms up she is your friend for life! Honey also loves really loves other dogs and so we are looking for a home that has a dog that can be Honey's bestie.

**PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING**

If you are interested in adopting any of the puppies, our adoption fee is $495 ( puppies) $375 (adults) which includes transportation from the South and we do suggest putting a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several littermates.

**Please understand that we are a volunteer based organization. While our volunteers try to answer all emails/questions as quickly as possible, below please find answers to some of our most frequently asked questions. We ask that you please read these FAQ's to see if your question has already been answered before emailing additional questions:

- If a dog or puppy is listed on Petfinder, they are still available. Please do not email asking if they are still available. If a dog or puppy is still listed, then we are still accepting applications :-) We do not go on a first come first serve basis, but on best fit for the family and most importantly, the puppy or dog.

- We are taking our best guess on breed and size when fully-grown (or already an adult), based on the puppy's/dog’s physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. We rarely are able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. 

- Our dogs/puppies are either at our Adoption Center in Brewster, NY, in foster care, or are adopted straight from transport. An application is necessary to meet any dog/puppy. Often, dogs and puppies are spoken for before they arrive. Many people feel more comfortable with a meet and greet which we completely understand and respect, however please know you are taking a chance of that puppy/dog getting adopted by someone else before hand.

- The way to start the process for any dog or puppy is by filling out an application. Applications for foster or adoption can be found at www.snarrnortheast.org and by clicking either adopt or foster from the main menu. If you fill out an application, please make sure you answer all the questions in as much detail as possible and that you receive a confirmation email, otherwise we did NOT receive it.

animal.description:
HEY EVERYONE!!!!!! I'm Dennis Daily!!! I was named by my 2 legged (7 year old ) foster brother after a famous Canadian Youtuber. lol! I actually like my name and answer to it regularly. My foster family calls me Denny or DenDen.
My rescue story began when I wandered up to a house in south central Iowa. I was cold, VERY hungry, and lost. I was found with burn marks on my neck from an e-collar. I am very trusting of women and children and most men. I LOVE to play with other dogs and people. I might do better with older children because when I get really excited, I can get a little mouthy. I love to play fetch....but sometimes I might just want to keep the toy for myself. :)
I think I was an outside dog up until I came to my foster home. Potty training has been going well. I am starting to understand I need to let my humans know I have to go outside. I am still trying to figure that one out. I am not a huge fan of pooping on the leash. AND I frequently get distracted with all the bird sounds. Birds are my favorite!!! I LOVE to chew!!! I am a typical 2 year old GSP. I am crate trained but still need more training on counter surfing (according to my foster mom). I'm not sure what she means.
My foster mom says I have a lot of potential for the perfect family. I can't wait to meet you!!!!

Complete the adoption form here : ADOPT ME

*Please be sure to read the adoption info/FAQ tab on our main website before applying for a dog. 2/2/21 2:19 PM

animal.description:
Hazel is 3 months old and 17 pounds.

She loves kids, other dogs and running. She is doing well on crate and house training but being a puppy you will need to continue training.

We have her listed as a staffy mix due to every puppy in the litter looks a little different. She looks like maybe some hound, lab, bully, etc. We expect her to be 50+ pounds as an adult.

Adoption fee is $125.00.

She is spayed, current on age appropriate vaccines and microchipped.

This is from her foster family:

Hey everyone! Meet little Princess Hazel. Her gorgeous eyes will lock you into her heart at first glance. Don't be fooled though, her kisses will literally seal the deal when you meet her. She has hippo-like squishey cheeks that complement her cute little snorts as she runs ? Princess Hazel runs like Goofy and is all over the place, but is getting faster every day! Princess Hazel likes to warn you of possible intruders, whether they are shadows, or you stubbing your toe on the corner of the wall. Either way, she tries to puff out little barks, with snorts at the end. This sweet girl is crate trained, and does amazing sleeping 10hrs a night with no accidents in her kennel. She also is crated when we leave the house for errands, and again with no accidents or whines/barks. Princess Hazel is spayed, microchipped, and up to date on her age-appropriate vaccines. Be sure to note, her paws are HUGE. This little girl will surely grow and grow and grow. She is going to be a big girl, but with a heart of gold, and a mission to kiss all the doggies with 2 legs or 4 legs. Oh, and she absolutely LOVES kiddos. Once she potties in the morning, she rushes up the stairs to jump in the kiddos beds and army crawl up to their face and smooch them good morning; all the while her tail is flapping super speed behind her. Her sharp, little puppy teeth are starting to fall out, so she needs good chew toys to keep her occupied as she is busy growing ? Princess Hazel thinks everything soft should be snuggled in, or rolled in, or tunneled in. As much as she loves to snuggle, her puppy zoomies can come out at any moment, which causes her to act like Bolt and take off in any direction, with her tail tucked for aerodynamics. Here in her foster home, she has 5 big foster doggy friends, and loves each one to the moon and back, and tries to get their whole faces wet with smooches every time she sees them. A happy, loving, silly girl is who Princess Hazel is. Don't you just want to meet her?

animal.description:
Meet Lennon, an approximately 11 week old pit mix who became a Misfit when she was 7 weeks old and in a rough shape. She needed to gain some weight and to learn how to love humans. This pet is spayed, up to date on all age-appropriate vaccinations and preventatives, heart-worm negative, and micro-chipped! If you are looking for an outgoing, full of life and personal companion that can go on daily adventures with you, then Lennon is your pup! 
Lennon is somewhat cautious in new situations, but it takes her no time at all to warm up to new people and show them how much fun she is. Lennon will make a perfect companion in about any home, she is just that great. She loves attention and playing with her humans and animal friends, but she will also entertain herself with a stick or chew toy. Lennon is a puppy, so if she is adopted to a home with small children, she will need help understanding the boundaries with the little ones. She has a very sweet demeanor, though, so little kids shouldn’t be a problem for her and she may actually enjoy running around with them. 
Lennon is good with cats and dogs of all sizes. She lives with several other foster puppies and several large breed dogs and does wonderful with all of them. She has the energy to match puppies her age, but she also tones it down for older dogs and likes to gently play with them as well. Lennon is still a puppy so she will need work on potty training and kennel training, but she is smart and will pick it up quickly. Lennon has been with other puppies in her foster home, so once she’s adopted, she will need some patience as she adjusts to being on her own. However, being more confident than her sister, she will adjust in no time, especially if she has a playmate.      

You can apply to meet / adopt this pet at www.muttmisfits.com/adoption-application!

animal.description:
Ruth is 3 months old and 17 pounds.

She loves kids, other dogs and running. She is doing well on crate and house training but being a puppy you will need to continue training.

We have her listed as a staffy mix due to every puppy in the litter looks a little different. She looks like maybe some hound, lab, bully, etc. We expect her to be 50+ pounds as an adult.

Adoption fee is $125.00

She is spayed, current on age appropriate vaccines and microchipped.

This is what her foster family has to say about Ruth:

Everyone say hello to Ruth....or as we call her Ruthie ? Ms. Ruth loves to run, and loves to be outside exploring and smelling all the world has to offer that day. Ms. Ruth loves to sneak attack her foster brothers and sisters, and then take off super fast so no one notices. She is a silly girl, and will chase a leaf blowing in the wind as long as she can. But leaves are not the only thing she loves to chase. Soccer balls, stuffed animals, sticks, and of course....shadows. Yes, shadows. She chases her own shadow full speed at night, until it disappears as she tuns around. Such a little goof. Happy....happy....happy....all the time. A soul to please all 2 legged and 4 legged doggies in this world ? She makes sure she does drive-by kisses, and may even ruffle up your hair as she does it, as she loves to burrow in hair. Ms. Ruth is an explorer at heart, and loves to take on adventures right beside my kiddos in the yard.  Her nose leads her to worms, and she will sniff and bark at them to let you know she has discovered something incredible! In pure puppy-ness, she needs lots of chew toys to keep her occupied, as she is starting to loose her little teeth, and growing into a big girl! Ms. Ruth has big puppy paws, so we know she will be a bigger girl once she is all grown up. She is very smart, and a fast learner. If you can't find her, do not worry.....simply call her by name, and she will come running, like she was called down for The Price is Right!!! ? Ms. Ruth is crate trained and has had no accidents when she is in her kennel. She sleeps in a kennel at night, and snores the night away for a good 10hrs. We also do crate her while we leave for errands, and she uses that time as her big girl nap time. Ms. Ruth is super excited when her people come home, and will forget about everything else until she gives you kisses to let you know how happy she is you came back ? She is spayed, microchipped, and up to date on age-appropriate vaccines. She will make an amazing companion, and with a lifetime of a happy-wagging tail, who could resist her sweet self!!

****PROTOCOLE COVID-19****

NOTRE REFUGE RESTE FERMÉ AU PUBLIC. LES ADOPTIONS SERONT GÉRÉES SUR RENDEZ-VOUS UNIQUEMENT LES SAMEDIS.  MERCI !

Mâle Berger Allemand croisé Labrador, né le 25 décembre 2015. Est arrivé au refuge suite à un déménagement. Maison et cour clôturée. Peut tirer en laisse. Propre, calme mais avec aussi une belle énergie, aime jouer avec des balles. Milieu non urbain et gens avec une bonne connaissance des chiens et très présents seront des atouts. Seuls les profils d’adoptants très complets seront analysés. 
Pas d’autres animaux ni enfants.

Dans l’espace prévu pour les commentaires, veuillez s’il vous plaît nous indiquer votre profil d’adoptant, à savoir tous les renseignements pertinents à votre sujet afin de constater si le chien pourrait être un bon match pour vous. Ainsi, votre expérience avec les chiens, si vous vivez en appartement ou maison, si votre cour est clôturée, les membres de votre famille, si vous avez d’autres animaux...Indiquez bien votre numéro de téléphone. 

SVP ne pas appeler le refuge pour les informations concernant nos animaux en adoption. Merci

Seules les demandes d’adoption retenues recevront un retour de courriel ou un appel téléphonique. 

Frais d’adoption: 340$, incluant la stérilisation, la vaccination et les vermifuges. Il n’y a pas de taxes. 

NOTE: il n’y a pas d’adoption avec enfants de 10 ans et moins



**** COVID-19 PROTOCOL****

OUR SHELTER REMAINS CLOSED TO THE PUBLIC.  ADOPTIONS WILL BE MANAGED BY APPOINTMENT ONLY ON SATURDAYS. THANK YOU !

Male German Shepherd mix Labrador born December 25, 2015. Arrived at the shelter following a move. House and fenced yard. Can pull on leash. House trained, calm but nice energy, likes to play balls very much. Non-urban environment and people with a good knowledge of dogs and very present will be assets. Only requests with a complete profile will be analyse.
 No other animals or children.

In the Comments box, please tell us about yourself and why you believe that this dog is a good match for you.  Please include your phone number, your dog experience, whether you live in an apartment or house, members of the household including pets, and whether you have a fenced in yard.  

Please do not call the shelter for information concerning our adoptable animals. Thank you!

Only successful adoption requests will receive a return email or a phone call.

Adoption Fee:  $ 340, including sterilization, vaccination and dewormer.   There are no taxes.

NOTE:  We do not adopt dogs to families with children 10 years of age and under.

animal.description:
Valentine's Day is right around the corner. Can Sasha be your forever sweetheart?

Sasha is a 3 year old 29 lb mixed breed. We don't know what makes Sasha Sasha, but our software says she is a Cirneco dell'Etna/Boston Terrier mix. Who even knows? We think she is a gremlin/rabbit mix!

When Sasha isn't impressing you with her athleticism, grace, and knowledge of obedience, she will make you laugh as she pulls out toy after toy from her basket and lies in the middle of her collection.

She is very smart and highly motivated and absolutely loves to learn! We think she would catch on to learning tricks easily. When she's not working her mind or her cute little booty, Sasha is an expert snuggler.

Sasha is extremely exuberant, and she doesn't always pay attention to cues from other dogs, so we think she'd do best as an only dog or in a home with a relaxed male. Sasha should not go to a house with cats. Sasha can be mouthy when she is overstimulated, so we do not recommend that she go into a home with children under the age of 12.
Sasha's adoption donation fee is $350, which includes spay/neuter, routine vetting and a microchip. You can apply for Sasha by filling out our online application, which is found on our website www.tarashouse.net or www.tarashouse.org. Please email us at info@tarashouse.net with any questions.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Name: Grace
Age:
Gender: Female
Breed: Pitty
Weight: 70
Dog friendly: Yes
Cat friendly: Yes
Kid friendly: Yes
House Trained: Yes
Crate Trained: Yes but does ok left out
Energy level: Moderate
History: Pulled from a shelter while pregnant, had 14 babies on transport to SHH
Adoption Fee: $500

From the Foster:

Grace is a calm, sweet girl who is so devoted to her puppies and her people. She came to us the day she was giving birth to her puppies in early December. She got to us just hours after having her last puppy and we rushed her home to get her settled into her own whelping room with her puppies. She was a tad protective the first few days which is extremely common, especially under the circumstances. She very quickly learned my husband and I were safe and within a few days we were wrapped around her paws.

There are a few things that Grace is going to need to work on. She is a tad nervous around men. Her favorite person now is my husband, however it took her a few days to trust him. So she will need a little patience around men and would need a home ready and willing to work on that. She also tries to play chase with our cat every once in a while. She has never been aggressive toward her, just likes to play so would do best in a home with either a dog savvy cat or no cats.

She is completely potty trained and will let you know when she has to go outside. She is not in a crate in our home at all as she is potty trained and such a good girl. She enjoys just lounging with our three small resident dogs while we are away. She does let you know when she has to go outside. She does amazing on a leash and loves her walks. She loves to snuggle on the couch and can't control her licker, she is always giving kisses. She has met kids ages one and up and has done great with all of them. She has done well around all other dogs she has met as well, no matter how small (our residents are 7, 10 and 14 pounds). She is a gem and is going to make an amazing family dog for a lucky family.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Little Lady Duchess is a 1(ish) year old yorkshire terrier mix. She has a lovely soft coat that does not seem to need a lot of maintenance. Duchess is originally from Texas and she is ready to start her new life in NY.

Duchess is full of fun and play. She likes other dogs and is very playful! Her fun loving spirit is contagious and she loves to get the other dogs to chase her in the yard. She loves to be outside and is getting used to this Buffalo weather! She can be outside for a bit and then she needs to come in and warm up but will go right back out once she is. She loves toys and balls. Duchess lives with other dogs and has no issues. She is good with cats but will bark on occasion just to see if she can get them to run so she can chase them around. It doesn't always work out for her lol. She has not been around kids in her foster home but if they are respectful of her, we don't expect issues. Duchess was initially nervous and shy for her foster mom but she traveled a long way and her life was turned upside down when she was disgarded by her family. There may be an adjustment period for her in her new home as she gets used to a new routine. She is good at going potty outside but will need additional training. She does use pee pads in her foster home too. She is crate trained and we just started working on her leash skills. Duchess loves to take naps with her foster mom and tries to weasle her way into her bed at night!

Duchess is spayed, up to date with vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated and tested neg for heartworm. Her adoption fee is $400

Link is a 2 yr old male chihuahua mix. He is neutered, UTD on vaccinations & microchipped. He weighs around 8lbs.

Link came to us as a stray & with us not knowing what he's been through, he does have separation anxiety. He will need a family that has the time & patience to work with him on this. He goes outside to potty when let out. He will need continued leash & harness training. He gets along with other dogs, women, men & kids. 

If you have lots of love to give Link, please complete an adoption application at www.pathwaysforpaws.com!

Adoption applications should be filled out to expedite the process:
http://www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org/joomla/adoption/adoption-application.html

Please Note, our adoptions are limited to the Austin Metro area.

This precious lil guy is estimated to be 12+. He loves to walk and goes a mile with no trouble. His only medical need is for eye drops which he will always require for a dry eye comdition.  Tramp is a sweet little gentleman who we feel was loved & well cared for during his life.  He is current on vaccines, heart worm negative, microchipped and on heartworm prevention . He licks his feet a lot and has been treated with Apoquel for allergies which didn’t have much effect. We think it is mostly habit but his foster mom cleans his feet after a walk. 

Tramp will gladly go out to go potty but can’t seem to manage a doggie door.  If his foster family needs to leave for an extended period they leave him In playpen with a pad for his Comfort and to prevent accidents. 

Adoption fee $350
** The Texas Comptroller now requires sales tax on adoption fees.

** Temporarily Suspended due to COVID **
Monthly Meet & Greets  (12:00 - 2:00)
Petco (in Leander) every 1st Saturday of the month
Pet Supplies Plus (Parmer & Mopac) every third Saturday of the month


** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process. Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.

Please call the shelter 516-869-6311 during working hours (Mon. to Fri. 9AM-4PM; Sat. 10-4PM) for more information about this Nala, the adoption process at the shelter and to confirm availability.  Please go to www.theshelterconnection.com or to the shelter page on Petfinder for more information about and directions to the shelter.
Nala is a gorgeous 5 year old Pit Bull Terrier that is unsure why she is in the shelter. Nala was surrendered with her sister when her family was moving and did not take the two of them with them. Her sister has since been adopted, but Nala still waits for her new home. Nala is sweet girl that loves her some treats, but sadly she is stressed here and therefore does not immediately interact with people meeting her. We believe that once this beautiful girl is home with a new, loving family she will come alive again. Due to the nervousness we are seeing here, we are not recommending her to live with young children at this time.
**Reminder** We are facilitating adoptions by appointment ONLY. If you arrive at the shelter without an appointment we will not be able to accommodate you. Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Everyone meet Jack This 4 year old boy with the handsome salt and pepper face is ready to meet his forever family. Jack has already been through the wringer in his short life, having been abandoned when his family moved, he ended up living in an empty house alone for a time. At some point he contracted heartworm, and he has a clean bill of health now! He is pretty athletic so he should be great on long walks and hikes.

He is happy and goofy, however he will need to be the only animal in the home.

He loves being outdoors and really enjoys the fresh air right inside as well, so a big backyard would be preferred and an Arizona room would be a bonus! He loves sunbathing and a good nap

He knows basic commands well, is crate trained and walks beautifully on a leash and is very food motivated, therefore is very trainable. The training he has now will need to be maintained longterm. Jack truly is a special gentleman and he will make one lucky family very happy!

animal.description:
Hi! Im NoDa! PIPs got me after a few months of not living my best life- and I am so glad they did! I am living in my fosters house with kids and other dogs, and while its takes me awhile to get used to the idea they are good-I still get nervous-I am really liking them all! The smallest kid is still a lot for me, so I dont know that a house with the little kids is best for me, but I do know I must have another dog! I follow my furry foster brother and sister anywhere, and if they do something so do I! Im slowly getting the whole I have to go potty outside thing- its like they want me to tell them or something! I will be sure to let them know when I am in my crate that I gotta go, and I think if they just keep giving me the good treats when I potty outside Ill get there!! I love my crate and my stuffy, and it is my space so if in there prefer to be left alone! Anything outside is fair game!

I know Im slow to get used to you, but man once I do Im a fun puppy living the puppy life! Busy balls and bones are my favorites- and I REALLY like mealtimes!!

animal.description:
DOB: 12/18/2018

Weight: 48 lbs

We are currently accepting applications to adopt Mila. If you are interested in meeting and adopting her, please submit an adoption application by visiting our website (www.HarborOfHopeDogRescue.org). Due to COVID19 safety measures, meetings are currently only being scheduled with approved adopters.

Mila is a 2 year old Rottweiler/Shar Pei mix who is a very playful and gentle girl. She is pretty shy when first meeting new people but if you give her a little time, she'll make it worth it! This girl LOVES zoomies, walks and getting the opportunity to slowly explore the world around her. She will need to have a fenced yard because of her love for zoomies.

At this time we are reccomending a home without kids under 12 due to how shy and sensitive she is to quick and unpredictable movement. We're still learning more about this girl, so please check back for more info!

 

All of our dogs are fully vetted before adoption, including vaccinations, spay/neuter, and a microchip.

The adoption process consists of an online application, a vet reference, two personal references, and a home visit. If approved to adopt, there is an adoption contract and an adoption amount. The adoption amount for Mila is $300 and goes toward the vetting and care of all the dogs in our rescue.

All adoptions will take place in the Omaha NE area and must be done in person. We are willing to adopt to out-of-state applicants, contingent on our ability to complete a home visit, but you must be willing to come to the Omaha area to complete the adoption. We do not ship, transport or deliver our dogs.

If you would like to learn more about Harbor of Hope Dog Rescue, please visit our website (www.HarborOfHopeDogRescue.org) or our Facebook page. Thank you for your support!

animal.description:
Rocco here! I'm 8 years young and I'm told I'm the perfect package. I dont disagree, that would be too much work! I enjoy the simple things in life like cuddling up on my human for a nice, long nap. I enjoy the company of other dogs, kids, any human at all really! I'm a happy, easy going guy just looking for the right family!

I sleep through the night because, who doesn't love to do that!? I also know how to be good in my crate and am mostly housebroken. I just need a few gentle reminders from time to time. If you enjoy a quiet laid back life like me, come meet me! I'll make you so loved!

Adoption fee is $195 and includes spay/neuter, microchip, fecal/deworming, vaccines and prevention up to date. Ohio residents only.

STS is a foster-based and volunteer-run rescue. We do not have a physical location or set hours for you to meet dogs, and it does take time to answer each inquiry. All dogs are in foster homes and once an application is approved and a home visit is completed you will be able to schedule meet and greets with available dogs. We encourage interested individuals to get approved prior to searching as it helps expedite the process. A Petfinder inquiry is not a substitute for an application. animal.description:
Hi, I am Pixel a Lab/Pointer Mix and I am almost 3 months old. I am a very energetic puppy that loves to run and play. I love toys and with the help of my sister, Siri, we find those crazy squeakers and kill them after we play with them some more. I know sit and I am working on other commands. Im also learning to walk on the leash not so sure about that yet. I will kennel up (especially if treats are involved). Im your typical rambunctious pup that just keeps on going. I really like people and love to get in lots of snuggles and kisses. I enjoy playing and wrestling with Siri. I have not played with other dogs yet but have met the neighbors bigger dogs and love to visit with them through the fence. I have not been exposed to cats. I will need someone with patience that is willing to work with me on my basic commands and potty training as I am not fully potty trained. You will need to teach me where to go and how to ask until I get the hang of it. I kennel at night and when my foster family is away. If you are looking for a puppy that will want LOTS of attention and you have the patience for a puppy, I may be what you are looking for. I will need toys or chew bones to keep me occupied, maybe a playmate and of course lots of snuggles and kisses from you.

I am ready to move into my new home anytime. I am scheduled to be spayed, I have been microchipped, dewormed and received my puppy shots along with rabies. My adoption fee is $400. Apply for me at www.bassetandbeagle.org if you are ready for a forever companion. I am currently fostered in Omaha NE.

animal.description:
PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO FOR REQUIREMENTS. NO PHONE CALLS PLEASE, EMAILS ONLY.

Meet Freda, our cute little female Chihuahua mix of 3 and a half years old and 15 lbs.

Freda's owner passed away and it was a very traumatic event for her. It has taken her time to come out of her shell and adopt, but she is a great little girl who deserves a loving and stable forever home.

Freda is house trained if taken out routinely on leash in the back yard, initially. She loves her crate. It is her safe place. She is a good eater and enjoys most other little dogs. She lives with 3 other small dogs right now in her foster home and is bonded to them.

She has also shown us that she loves cats! We think she thinks she is a cat sometimes! She often would snuggle with a foster cat who was in her foster home, it was so cute!

Freda just needs time to acclimate to a new setting, and once she does, she will be an amazing family pet. We would prefer to not place her in a home with kids. Ideally, her new home will be with adults only who are dog savvy, and with another dog (or cat who likes dogs) for her to have a buddy. 

She requires a secure fenced in yard and applicants must live within 30 mins of Tulsa.

Email us about her today. We would love to hear from you at amyh@rescuednready.com. Applications are found at www.rescuednready.com.


ADOPTIONS ONLY TO PEOPLE LIVING IN THE NORTHEASTERN OKLAHOMA AREA.  

The adoption fee is $225.00 and includes all current vaccinations, negative heartworm test, worming, microchip, and spay/neuter surgery.  Go to www.rescuednready.com to learn about our adoption process and download our application.  

CALL or EMAIL US TO MEET ONE OF OUR ADOPTABLE DOGS! Call Amy at 918-688-0755 or email at amyh@rescuednready.com.

LIKE RESCUED 'N READY ON FACEBOOK!!

PLEASE READ: The clinics are not open for viewing animals. Since we currently can't meet you in person, if you are interested in meeting this pet, please email information about yourself, family, residence and current/prior pet experience. If it is a good fit you will be emailed an application. Once that is approved, arrangements will be made for a meeting. Thanks for your understanding!

Meet Dot! Dot is a Lab x Chihuahua? That was born around 11/2/20. Unfortunately we don't have much information on Dot's background other than she came from Kentucky as an owner surrender along with Yakko and Wakko (who are from a separate, slightly older litter. Possibly related?). Dot is a sweet and friendly puppy. Her adoption fee is $399 and includes her spay, microchip, vaccinations and routine labwork. Please email us to start the adoption process.

For adoptions of puppies 6 months old or younger, you must reside within 50 miles of Shorewood, IL.



Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes:
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*:
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old)
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt:

If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

animal.description:
Hello, my name is Thurston. I am estimated to be about 6-7 months old, though my breed is unknown; guessing maybe Black Mouthed Cur?  I was found cold and shivering in a falling-down tin shack barn in South Corpus Christi.  At that time, I was having trouble moving so local neighbors were leaving food for me.  Then my wonderful foster family took me in and it was found that I had multiple small fractures on my pelvis and a fracture in my neck.  They nursed me back to good health and now I'm bouncing around with my buddy Astro, who was another rescue dog.  I do have a crooked tail that was from another injury that happened before I was rescued by Cuz i Matter Animal Rescue.  My foster Mom has said that I am just the sweetest pup and that I am also potty trained.

I am looking for a good loving home to call my own, with lots of attention from the new adopters.  If you'd like more information about me, please send CiMAR an email so they can send you all the information about adopting me.  You can also find more pictures of me on their website:  http://www.cuzimatter.org/adopt-a-dog.

animal.description:
Age: ~ 1 year (as of 01/21/21)
Weight: 38.6 lbs (as of 01/21/21)

Location: RI

This dog has been spayed/neutered, is up to date on shots, on heartworm preventative and is microchipped.

Light wants to please!

This handsome boy would like to bring a little light into your life! We are thinking Light is a Lab mix about 1-year-old.

He grew up in an outside pen with his brothers and sisters, but little human interaction. He is gentle and respectful with adults and children he knows but we don't yet know how he is with new people. Light appears to be behind in socialization with people, other pets, and new places. A potential adopter will need to keep this in mind and go slow, work on socialization, give him plenty of exercise, and provide training and structure as he transitions to life in a forever home. He would do best in a low-key household without much foot traffic, no young children, and lots of patience and treats!

Light likes other dogs but they need to be introduced slowly, one at a time. We don't know if he has lived with cats, but tends to be unengaged with the ones he has seen. He is a quiet boy who rarely barks.

Light appears to be house trained and crate trained, so he has had some training. He does need some work on his leash skills as he initially bucks but he will eventually settle and walk calmly.

Light needs an adopter who is committed to keeping his world small until he starts to settle in. The adopter should plan to limit visitors to his home, leave the dog at home (crated - not loose!) rather than taking him to parties, soccer games, dog parks, etc, and focus on building a bond through structure and moderate obedience training. A fenced yard would be ideal so he could run and play safely, but if that's not available he'll need lots of leash walks and opportunities for off-leash play in a fenced area.

Light a gentle happy boy who just wants a loving forever home. Can you make his dream come true? Fill out an application today and let him know that you'd love to have him join your family!

Adoption Fee: $585

To apply for this dog, fill out an adoption application on our website: www.sosarl.org/aa/

**Additional info you should know - For most of our dogs, we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each of our dogs as an individual and do our best to describe and place them based on personality not breed label. Some dogs may not yet be in New England, nor ready for immediate adoption. There may be additional vetting, quarantine, waiting periods and/or fees depending upon your state of residence. If you have questions or concerns on any of this, you can discuss this with your Adoption Counselor.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Our sweet little Ice Cream puppies are ready for their new homes! This litter came to us after their mama got hit by a car :-( they needed to be kept safe! They are little chihuahua mixes, just over 3 months old.

The puppies are full of life! There is never a dull moment with 6 puppies running around! They are very playful, sometimes rough but always ready for cuddles with their foster family. They live with other dogs of various sizes in their foster home and do well with everyone. They like the house cats too! Although they have not been exposed to kids while in rescue, we do not believe there will be an issue as long as the kids are kind and respectful of their small statures. Housetraining is still a skill in need of work - right now they use pee pads. One or two will venture outside into the snow but then quickly hightail it back inside! They love toys and chewies are a favorite. They are gated or penned at night and when their foster family is gone for the day. They still need training and that

Moose is one of 3 boys and the biggest. And the biggest baby! He is very sensitive and will let you know if his feelings are hurt. He is a active little dog - he follows his foster mom everywhere. He learned stairs and still tells his foster mom every time he goes up and down lol. He goes outside with the 'big dogs' but doesn't really know why he's out there other then to play. Moose loves to be held and babied! This little boy is looking forward to a life time of being spoiled!

Moose Tracks is neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated at the time. His adoption fee is $400

animal.description: Meet Charlie! Charlie joined our Satchel's family recently when his family had a change in living circumstances and could no longer keep him. He's an affectionate one year-old Boxer/Catahoula mix who loves going for long walks and car rides with his favorite volunteers. At 70 pounds, Charlie is a large boy and can be quite a strong puller on walks. He loves playing with stuffed toys and can often be seen playing quietly in his kennel with his collection of toys. Charlie is a bit insecure meeting strangers but we have found with a proper introduction, he quickly becomes comfortable with new people. Although Charlie formerly lived with small dogs and cats, he does show some reactivity to dogs in our shelter environment. Several successful meet and greets would be required for any potential canine or feline siblings. If you would like to meet Charlie, please fill out an adoption application (no obligation) at www.satchelslastresort.org, and an adoption counselor will be in touch.

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Bullseye! I have been waiting patiently for my turn to get a forever home! It is finally here and I am psyched. I am about 70 lbs and 1.5 years old. I am great with my doggie foster siblings. I do seem to be more comfortable and prefer the females though - not mean to the males, just think I like the ladies more! I would be just fine as an only in my new home or with a female that would play with me! I am housebroken and good in the crate. I am a young guy so will require some guidance and of course exercise; someone who understands my breed is a plus. I am a cuddly big dude who really loves his people and would make a great addition to an adult home; I have some spent some time with younger kids but can be big and a little jumpy so might knock down little ones; school-aged kids might appreciate me more!   ASCZ has no idea on how I would be with a cat so likely that isn't the best idea! :) Please email erin@asecondchnaceforziva.com for more info on handsome me!

animal.description:
Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes. Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!
Additionally for CATS you may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com

Say Hello to Oreo! A sweet and smart Pit Bull/Cattle Dog mix, Oreo is a very high energy girl that will thrive in an active environment that allows her the room and time to run/jump/play. At approximately 9 months of age, she weighs in the 35lb.-40 lb. range. Looking for a buddy to chase outdoors, play tug of war, or just snuggle? She's your girl! Oreo is making good progress on leash/kennel/potty training. She is spayed, heartworm negative, and current on vaccinations. Because of her size, strength, and enthusiasm level (she greets with a body wag and a tail wag), Oreo will do best with other dogs who have her same energy level and size range. She is not good with cats or smaller dogs. Oreo's new home must have a secure 6ft. wooden fence. She does love her humans, and is best suited for a home with a pet parents who have experience with her breed(s)/similar breeds and children over the age of 14 (no small children). For more information on Oreo, please contact gapfosterfriday@gmail.com

animal.description:
This goofy girl's name is Daisy. Daisy is a bundle of happiness and energy and is an absolute sweetheart! She is a Walker Coonhound and is believed to be around six-years-old. Daisy loves the outdoors and seems to know her way around the woods quite well which is typical for her breed. She does not seem reactive to other dogs but due to her past we are not sure how she would do living with one. She is definitely not a fan of cats and has no problem speaking her voice about them with her deep howl.
Daisy arrived at our shelter VERY pregnant and gave birth to 10 beautiful puppies. She was a great Mom and now it's her turn to find her forever home with a great family who understands (and loves) her breed!Please visit the following link on our website to learn about Second Chance's adoption process. http://www.2ndchanceanimalcenter.org/adoption.html

animal.description: With his long legs and silky gray fur, Earl is a big, gorgeous hunk of a dog. Earl can be a bit shy when meeting new people but will open up once he realizes he is safe. Earl does great with dogs big and small. He currently lives in a house with cats, the kitties tend to stay away, and he has shown minimal interest. Earl has lots of playful energy so will do best with a dog that has similar energy, and because he is a shyguy, a confident dog will do best to help him build his confidence. Earl needs a fenced in yard (he is a little shy about going potty on a leash). As for his humans, someone patient to get him through his shy times, and as you can see in his pictures, someone ok with him truly believing he is a 60+ lb lapdog.
