Calling all Shepherd (mix) lovers! Katarina is a happy, loving dog. She's shy at first but gets attached to her human very quickly. She's housebroken, walks well on the leash and knows basic commands. She's a low-key girl...if not lazy! She loves attention, especially belly rubs, but is happy to just hang out next to her human all day. What a perfect sweetheart!

Katarina has typical Shepherd tendencies and can be protective of her human, so she would probably do best as an only dog. If you are an experienced dog owner fill out an application today to make Katarina your new best pal!!

Cuddly, CottonBall CAYLEE has come to DASH ready for her Forever Family to find them!
CAYLEE is a gentle, loving and CALM breed mix 13 weeks old and 19 lbs; she will be a large dog but NOT a giant when full-grown, maybe 60 lbs, and she appears to have the BEST traits from a Husky/"Winter Breed" with the much lower shedding, tightly-woven fur of a Pyrenees.
CAYLEE LOVES TO PLAY indoors and out as she's always had her brother as a built-in playmate - however she is happy to play with any gentle large dog and can run & roll around the yard in the sun a couple of hours as long as she has a playmate.
On the flip side she is also EXTREMELY well-behaved indoors. She wants to follows her humans and our other dogs around the house and can flop down with one of us to relax and snooze. Much calmer than most young puppies but healthy and lively and acclimating to whatever environments she has been in.
CAYLEE is crate-trained but doesn't love the crate until she's worn-out, but she's also been AMAZING with house-breaking and can sleep all night without needing to be restricted as long as she sticks to her feeding schedule and gets several chances to be let outdoors for a few minutes.
If you're interested in meeting this lovable white, fluffy, cotton-ball of sweetness and softness please complete our application on our site listed below then text Sara at 214-549-9905 so I can review your application!
www.dashdog.org

General Info - PLEASE READ! *Our $350 adoption fee is based on the cost of rescuing, transporting and vetting each dog; we do not try to compete on prices with municipal shelters whose funds are paid by the city. Our philosophy is to rescue highly adoptable dogs, have them live kennel-free in private homes for temperament assessments and individual personalities.
We work hard to match EACH dog with the right family - kids or no kids, other dogs male or female and/or cats. With very rare exceptions all dogs over 6 months will be spayed or neutered PRIOR to adoption - dogs under 6 months will include a spay/neuter date AND referral info for lower-cost surgery if the adopter does not choose to use her or his personal vet. OUR VETS WILL NOT PERFORM SPAY NEUTER SURGERIES UNTIL DOG IS 6 MONTHS OLD.

Please READ ALL of our info below BEFORE SENDING APPLICATION.

Our goal is to help our puppies and dogs find FOREVER HOMES AND FAMILIES, NOT TO MAKE IT PROHIBITIVE FOR YOU TO ADOPT. However, once we review the application and contact you, we MEET TO ADOPT, so please let us know if you are ONLY APPLYING TO STAY ON FILE or THAT YOU ARE READY TO ADOPT, for the consideration of our puppies and dogs and families who know the time is right!

animal.description:
Meet Pam!  This sweet little beagle is about 9 months old and is looking for her furever family.  Pam is dog social but likes to be the boss of her canine companions, so she needs friends who will tolerate her outgoing nature. She is sweet and loves being around both people and dogs. Pam is very interested in cats but is good as long as they are tolerant of a dog being in their business. Pam is very active and would love a fenced yard so she can spend lots of time running and exploring. She will find a toy and spend hours flinging it around the yard then pouncing on it. Being a true Beagle, her nose tells her where she’s going so she wouldn’t do well without a fence. 

Pam will require someone who is basically always home or takes her everywhere as she has severe separation anxiety. A family where everyone works away from home or leaves her home alone for long periods is not a good match for Pam. She has learned to be independent when her foster family takes short trips away from the house, but she needs food puzzles and a Furbo to stay busy.  And she really responds to praise for good behavior after her family makes a quick trip to the store.

Pam knows that she has some special requirements and it might take time for her to find the perfect home.  But, if someone will give her the chance, she promises to be a loving companion and shower her new family in beagle antics for years to come.  If you would like more information on adding Pam to your pack, please contact her adoption consultant, Kelly, at Kelgirl1077@yahoo.com  Pam can’t wait to meet you!
